latestPosts.caption:
I started working in social media when I was 16, managing content from a farm in rural North Dakota—26 miles from the nearest grocery store but just a click away from the rest of the world. What started as a side hustle became a passion, leading me to build a career in content creation, brand growth, and collaborations with some of the biggest names in fashion, lifestyle, and travel.

But something was missing—an agency that truly understands creators from the inside out. So, I made the leap. In December, I quit my corporate cybersecurity tech sales job to launch my dream. I left behind a stable career to create something that genuinely empowers creators—the kind of agency I wish had existed when I was starting out.

Introducing The North Management—a next-generation influencer marketing agency, built by creators, for creators. We’re here to help brands and influencers scale, collaborate, and get paid what they deserve.

Alongside my co-founder @jon.ilani, we’re kicking things off with an incredible roster of talent. 

Follow @thenorthmanagement for the latest.
latestPosts.alt: Photo by Evan Braaten in Minneapolis, Minnesota with @thenorthmanagement.
